      • onBlockPlace

        public void onBlockPlace(BlockPlaceEvent event)
        Description copied from class: BaseSTBBlock
        Called when an STB block has been placed. The physical block has not yet been placed in the world, but the block is already registered as an STB block, and placement will definitely happen at this point. This method is called after BaseSTBBlock.placeBlock(org.bukkit.block.Block, org.bukkit.entity.Player, org.bukkit.block.BlockFace)

        This event is called with MONITOR priority; do not change the outcome of the event!

        Overrides:
        onBlockPlace in class BaseSTBBlock
        Parameters:
        event - the block place event

      • onBlockBreak

        public void onBlockBreak(BlockBreakEvent event)
        Description copied from class: BaseSTBBlock
        Called when an STB block is actually broken. At the point of calling, the block (and any possible auxiliary blocks) will have already been set to AIR and the STB block will have been unregistered.

        The event handler runs with MONITOR priority; you must not alter the outcome of this event!

        Overrides:
        onBlockBreak in class BaseSTBBlock
        Parameters:
        event - the block break event

      • getTickRate

        public int getTickRate()
        Description copied from class: BaseSTBBlock
        Defines the rate at which the block ticks. BaseSTBBlock.onServerTick() will be called this frequently. Override this method to have the block tick less frequently. The default rate of 0 means that the block will not tick at all.
        Overrides:
        getTickRate in class BaseSTBBlock

      • onServerTick

        public void onServerTick()
        Description copied from class: BaseSTBBlock
        Called every tick for each STB block that is placed in the world, for any STB block where BaseSTBBlock.getTickRate() returns a non-zero value. Override this method to define any periodic behaviour of the block.
